<title>FINLAND: NORDEL SUPPORTS NORDIC POWER BOURSE IN 1997 -IVO.</title>
<headline>NORDEL SUPPORTS NORDIC POWER BOURSE IN 1997 -IVO.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Finnish electricity producer Imatran Voima (IVO) said in a statement on Friday that the Nordic utilities' association Nordel suppports the introduction of a pan-Nordic electricity exchange already next year.</p>
<p>There are currently two separate power exchanges in the Nordic countries -- one in Norway led by the Swedish and Finnish state-owned grid operators and one in Finland run by derivatives exchange SOM -- but trade on the two could be merged, it said.</p>
<p>&quot;However, a requirement is that that technical and administrative prerequisities such as grid charges and other market terms be harmonised,&quot; it noted.</p>
<p>Electricity taxation would also have to be harmonised, it said.</p>
<p>Trade on the Finnish exchange started only one week ago.</p>
<p>-- Helsinki newsroom +358-0-6805 0245</p>
</text>
